23/04/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Two ethnic Albanian lawmakers submitted a draft law Thursday (April 22nd) on the status of former National Liberation Army (NLA) fighters from the 2001 conflict.
The bill, proposed by Abedin Zumberi from the New Democracy party and independent Daut Rexhepi, requires the support of 15 lawmakers for parliamentary consideration.
The draft law envisions benefits for the families of NLA fighters killed in action, disabled people and civilians affected by the conflict.
In other news Thursday, several NGOs representing ethnic Albanians announced they will organise protests on May 10th against they what they describe as "discriminatory policy based on ethnic and religious grounds".
(Alsat, Sitel, Dnevnik, AP - 22/04/10)
